│  Final Answer:                                                                                                  │
│  I propose augmenting the Morgan fingerprint representation with physicochemical descriptors and switching to   │
│  a gradient boosting model.                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                 │
│  What to change:                                                                                                │
│  1. Keep Morgan fingerprints but expand to 2048 bits at radius 3 for richer substructural context               │
│  2. Add MACCS keys (166 structural keys capturing pharmacophore patterns)                                       │
│  3. Add 6 RDKit physicochemical descriptors: MolLogP, TPSA, MolWt, NumHDonors, NumHAcceptors,                   │
│  NumRotatableBonds                                                                                              │
│  4. Replace LogisticRegression with HistGradientBoostingClassifier (sklearn)                                    │
│                                                                                                                 │
│  Why it should improve performance:                                                                             │
│  BBB penetration is governed by lipophilicity (LogP), polar surface area (TPSA), and molecular size (MW) per    │
│  the Pardridge model. Morgan fingerprints alone capture local substructure but miss these global                │
│  physicochemical properties. MACCS keys add expert-curated functional group detection. Gradient boosting        │
│  handles the mixed binary/continuous feature space and captures nonlinear interactions between lipophilicity    │
│  and hydrogen bonding that LogisticRegression cannot model.                                                     │
│                                                                                                                 │
│  Expected improvement: 3-6 percent ROC-AUC gain, targeting 0.93-0.95. This estimate is based on published       │
│  MoleculeNet benchmarks where fingerprint fusion with physicochemical descriptors consistently improves ADMET   │
│  prediction tasks.                                                                                              │
